:!<command> #execute linux command
---
### **Modes**
* `Normal` – navigate, delete, yank, etc. (default)
* `Insert` – type text (`i`, `I`, `a`, `A`, `o`, `O`)
* `Visual` – select text (`v`, `V`, `Ctrl+v`)
* `Command-line` – enter commands (`:`)
---
### **Movement**
* `h` left, `j` down, `k` up, `l` right
* `w` next word, `b` back word, `e` end of word
* `0` start of line, `^` first non-blank, `$` end of line
* `gg` top of file, `G` bottom of file
* `{` previous paragraph, `}` next paragraph
* `Ctrl+f` page down, `Ctrl+b` page up
---
### **Editing**
* `x` delete char, `dd` delete line, `D` delete to end of line
* `yy` yank line, `p` paste after, `P` paste before
* `u` undo, `Ctrl+r` redo
* `r<char>` replace one char
* `~` toggle case
---
### **Visual Mode**
* `v` select chars, `V` select lines, `Ctrl+v` select block
* `y` yank selection, `d` delete selection, `>` indent, `<` unindent
---
### **Search & Replace**
* `/pattern` search forward, `?pattern` search backward
* `n` next match, `N` previous match
* `:%s/old/new/g` replace all
---
### **Windows & Tabs**
* `:split` or `:sp` horizontal split
* `:vsplit` or `:vsp` vertical split
* `Ctrl+w h/j/k/l` move between splits
* `:tabnew` new tab, `:tabnext` next tab, `:tabprev` previous tab
---
### **Files**
* `:w` save, `:q` quit, `:wq` save & quit, `:q!` quit without saving
* `:e filename` open file, `:bnext` / `:bprev` buffer switch
---
### **Clipboard**
* `"+y` copy to system clipboard
* `"+p` paste from system clipboard
---
### **Misc**
* `.` repeat last action
* `:set number` show line numbers
* `:set relativenumber` relative line numbers
* `:help <command>` get help
*  :g/^$/d  delete blank lines g-to all matching ^start of line $-end of line -d delete
